const _astro_dataLayerContent = [["Map",1,2,9,10],"meta::meta",["Map",3,4,5,6,7,8],"astro-version","5.15.6","content-config-digest","4b73ce5200facea3","astro-config-digest","{\"root\":{},\"srcDir\":{},\"publicDir\":{},\"outDir\":{},\"cacheDir\":{},\"site\":\"https://youfixit.co.uk\",\"compressHTML\":true,\"base\":\"/\",\"trailingSlash\":\"ignore\",\"output\":\"static\",\"scopedStyleStrategy\":\"attribute\",\"build\":{\"format\":\"directory\",\"client\":{},\"server\":{},\"assets\":\"_astro\",\"serverEntry\":\"entry.mjs\",\"redirects\":true,\"inlineStylesheets\":\"auto\",\"concurrency\":1},\"server\":{\"open\":false,\"host\":false,\"port\":4321,\"streaming\":true,\"allowedHosts\":[]},\"redirects\":{},\"image\":{\"endpoint\":{\"route\":\"/_image\"},\"service\":{\"entrypoint\":\"astro/assets/services/sharp\",\"config\":{}},\"domains\":[],\"remotePatterns\":[],\"responsiveStyles\":false},\"devToolbar\":{\"enabled\":true},\"markdown\":{\"syntaxHighlight\":{\"type\":\"shiki\",\"excludeLangs\":[\"math\"]},\"shikiConfig\":{\"langs\":[],\"langAlias\":{},\"theme\":\"github-dark\",\"themes\":{},\"wrap\":false,\"transformers\":[]},\"remarkPlugins\":[],\"rehypePlugins\":[],\"remarkRehype\":{},\"gfm\":true,\"smartypants\":true},\"security\":{\"checkOrigin\":true,\"allowedDomains\":[]},\"env\":{\"schema\":{},\"validateSecrets\":false},\"experimental\":{\"clientPrerender\":false,\"contentIntellisense\":false,\"headingIdCompat\":false,\"preserveScriptOrder\":false,\"liveContentCollections\":false,\"csp\":false,\"staticImportMetaEnv\":false,\"chromeDevtoolsWorkspace\":false,\"failOnPrerenderConflict\":false},\"legacy\":{\"collections\":false}}","guides",["Map",11,12],"ram",{id:11,data:13,body:19,filePath:20,assetImports:21,digest:23,rendered:24},{title:14,description:15,heroImage:16,pubDate:17,updatedDate:18},"Upgrade or Replace RAM","A practical, step-by-step guide to upgrading or replacing RAM with placeholders you can customise.","__ASTRO_IMAGE_./placeholder-hero.svg",["Date","2025-11-17T00:00:00.000Z"],["Date","2025-11-18T00:00:00.000Z"],"# Upgrade or Replace RAM\n\nThis guide walks through upgrading or replacing the RAM in a desktop or laptop — with clear, tweakable steps and placeholder images you can replace with real photos.\n\n\n- **Estimated time:** 10–30 minutes\n- **Difficulty:** Easy–Medium (depending on device)\n- **What you need:** Screwdriver (if applicable), compatible RAM modules, antistatic precautions\n\n## Before you start — Safety\n\n1. Shut down and unplug the machine.\n2. Ground yourself (antistatic wrist strap or touch metal chassis).\n3. Work on a clean, flat surface with good light.\n\n## Steps\n\nBelow is a concise set of steps. The page layout renders these as a \"Quick Steps\" block above the full article. You can edit the `steps` frontmatter to customise titles, descriptions, and images.\n\n---\n\n## Detailed procedure\n\n### 1 — Identify existing RAM and slots\n\nOpen the case or access panel and note the number of modules and free slots. Look for labels on the modules for DDR generation and speed.\n\n### 2 — Choose compatible replacements\n\nMatch the DDR generation (for example DDR4), the form factor (DIMM or SODIMM), and a similar or higher speed. For best results, buy from a single kit if using multiple modules.\n\n### 3 — Install the modules\n\nIf replacing modules: gently press out the side clips and remove the sticks. Align the notch and press the new module straight down until clips engage.\n\n### 4 — Boot and verify\n\nPower on and enter BIOS/UEFI to verify the new capacity and frequency. In the OS, check system info or use memory tests (e.g., MemTest86) if you want to validate stability.\n\n## Customisation notes\n\n- Replace the `heroImage` and `steps[*].image` paths with real photos in `public/assets/`.\n- Add or remove steps in frontmatter — the layout will render them automatically.\n\n---\n\nIf you'd like, I can replace the placeholder SVGs with real device photos, or add a simple table showing common DDR speeds and part numbers.","src/content/guides/ram.md",[22],"./placeholder-hero.svg","e5e704e6c126356b",{html:25,metadata:26},"<h1 id=\"upgrade-or-replace-ram\">Upgrade or Replace RAM</h1>\n<p>This guide walks through upgrading or replacing the RAM in a desktop or laptop — with clear, tweakable steps and placeholder images you can replace with real photos.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Estimated time:</strong> 10–30 minutes</li>\n<li><strong>Difficulty:</strong> Easy–Medium (depending on device)</li>\n<li><strong>What you need:</strong> Screwdriver (if applicable), compatible RAM modules, antistatic precautions</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"before-you-start--safety\">Before you start — Safety</h2>\n<ol>\n<li>Shut down and unplug the machine.</li>\n<li>Ground yourself (antistatic wrist strap or touch metal chassis).</li>\n<li>Work on a clean, flat surface with good light.</li>\n</ol>\n<h2 id=\"steps\">Steps</h2>\n<p>Below is a concise set of steps. The page layout renders these as a “Quick Steps” block above the full article. You can edit the <code>steps</code> frontmatter to customise titles, descriptions, and images.</p>\n<hr>\n<h2 id=\"detailed-procedure\">Detailed procedure</h2>\n<h3 id=\"1--identify-existing-ram-and-slots\">1 — Identify existing RAM and slots</h3>\n<p>Open the case or access panel and note the number of modules and free slots. Look for labels on the modules for DDR generation and speed.</p>\n<h3 id=\"2--choose-compatible-replacements\">2 — Choose compatible replacements</h3>\n<p>Match the DDR generation (for example DDR4), the form factor (DIMM or SODIMM), and a similar or higher speed. For best results, buy from a single kit if using multiple modules.</p>\n<h3 id=\"3--install-the-modules\">3 — Install the modules</h3>\n<p>If replacing modules: gently press out the side clips and remove the sticks. Align the notch and press the new module straight down until clips engage.</p>\n<h3 id=\"4--boot-and-verify\">4 — Boot and verify</h3>\n<p>Power on and enter BIOS/UEFI to verify the new capacity and frequency. In the OS, check system info or use memory tests (e.g., MemTest86) if you want to validate stability.</p>\n<h2 id=\"customisation-notes\">Customisation notes</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Replace the <code>heroImage</code> and <code>steps[*].image</code> paths with real photos in <code>public/assets/</code>.</li>\n<li>Add or remove steps in frontmatter — the layout will render them automatically.</li>\n</ul>\n<hr>\n<p>If you’d like, I can replace the placeholder SVGs with real device photos, or add a simple table showing common DDR speeds and part numbers.</p>",{headings:27,localImagePaths:57,remoteImagePaths:58,frontmatter:59,imagePaths:75},[28,31,35,38,41,45,48,51,54],{depth:29,slug:30,text:14},1,"upgrade-or-replace-ram",{depth:32,slug:33,text:34},2,"before-you-start--safety","Before you start — Safety",{depth:32,slug:36,text:37},"steps","Steps",{depth:32,slug:39,text:40},"detailed-procedure","Detailed procedure",{depth:42,slug:43,text:44},3,"1--identify-existing-ram-and-slots","1 — Identify existing RAM and slots",{depth:42,slug:46,text:47},"2--choose-compatible-replacements","2 — Choose compatible replacements",{depth:42,slug:49,text:50},"3--install-the-modules","3 — Install the modules",{depth:42,slug:52,text:53},"4--boot-and-verify","4 — Boot and verify",{depth:32,slug:55,text:56},"customisation-notes","Customisation notes",[],[],{title:14,description:15,pubDate:60,heroImage:22,steps:61,updatedDate:74},"2025-11-17",[62,66,70],{title:63,description:64,image:65},"Identify your hardware","Power down, open the case and check the existing RAM modules for type and capacity. Match DDR generation, speed and physical form factor (DIMM vs SODIMM).","/assets/placeholder-step-1.svg",{title:67,description:68,image:69},"Choose compatible RAM","Pick modules that match or are compatible with your motherboard and CPU. Prefer dual-channel pairs and check the motherboard QVL if needed.","/assets/placeholder-step-2.svg",{title:71,description:72,image:73},"Install the new modules","Seat the modules firmly into the slots until the side clips click. If replacing, remove old modules first and keep them in antistatic bags.","/assets/placeholder-step-3.svg","2025-11-18",[]];

